<!DOCTYPE html>
<html data-theme-preference="<%= AppSetting.get('theme') || 'auto' %>">
  <head>
    <%# Title is built with safe_join rather than string interpolation so
        HTML entities embedded in the page title (such as apostrophe
        entities from a project name) survive untouched. A plain yield
        plus " ~ pito" interpolation would drop the SafeBuffer status
        and re-escape entities into the browser tab; safe_join keeps
        the SafeBuffer contract end-to-end. (Note: this comment used
        to mention an ERB output tag literal, which contained the
        sequence that closes a comment block, and that broke document
        parsing — see fix on 2026-05-06.) %>
    <title><%= content_for?(:title) ? safe_join([yield(:title), " ~ pito"]) : "pito ~ best YouTube tool" %></title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="application-name" content="Pito">
    <meta name="turbo-refresh-method" content="morph">
    <meta name="turbo-refresh-scroll" content="preserve">
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    <%= csp_meta_tag %>

    <%= yield :head %>

    <%# Phase 7.5 — MCP custom-connector icon discovery. Claude.ai's
        connector probe path isn't documented; we shotgun every
        reasonable surface so whichever path Claude actually checks
        resolves to the Pito logo (red P). Surfaces covered:
          - `<link rel="icon">` — generic favicon hint
          - `<link rel="apple-touch-icon">` (bare + 180x180) — Apple
            convention some clients reuse for square logos
          - `<meta property="og:*">` — Open Graph image, absolute URL
            (required by the OG spec)
          - `<link rel="manifest">` — web app manifest at
            `/manifest.json` listing `/Pito.png` as the icon
          - `/favicon.ico` route alias (`config/routes.rb`) → 301 to
            `/Pito.png` for clients that ONLY check `.ico`.
        See `app/controllers/well_known_controller.rb` for the
        OAuth-metadata `logo_uri` extension. %>
    <link rel="icon" href="/Pito.png" type="image/png">
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/Pito.png">
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/Pito.png">
    <link rel="manifest" href="/manifest.json">
    <meta property="og:title" content="pito">
    <meta property="og:description" content="best YouTube tool">
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://app.pitomd.com/Pito.png">

    <%= stylesheet_link_tag :app, "data-turbo-track": "reload" %>
    <script>
      (function() {
        var s = localStorage.getItem("pito-theme");
        if (s === "light" || s === "dark") { document.documentElement.setAttribute("data-theme", s); return; }
        var p = document.documentElement.dataset.themePreference;
        if (p === "light" || p === "dark") { document.documentElement.setAttribute("data-theme", p); return; }
        document.documentElement.setAttribute("data-theme", window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)").matches ? "dark" : "light");
      })();
    </script>
    <%= javascript_importmap_tags %>
  </head>

  <body data-controller="keyboard">
    <header style="position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 32px; background: var(--color-bg); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding: 0 12px; z-index: 100;" data-controller="theme">
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; height: 32px; gap: 6px;">
        <a href="/" style="text-decoration: none; display: flex; align-items: center; line-height: 0;" aria-label="Dashboard">
          <img src="/Pito.png" alt="Pito" class="header-logo">
        </a>
        <%# Chrome elements (nav, search, logout, keyboard help link) are
            suppressed on auth pages by setting
            `content_for(:hide_chrome, true)` from the page template. The
            header logo and theme toggle remain visible so the brand and
            the dark/light affordance are always available. The same flag
            also gates the footer nav (see footer block below). %>
        <% unless content_for?(:hide_chrome) %>
          <nav class="dot-list"><span class="hide-mobile"><%= nav_link "home", root_path %></span><%= nav_link "channels", channels_path, short: "C" %><%= nav_link "videos", videos_path, short: "V" %><%= nav_link "projects", projects_path, short: "P" %><%= nav_link "settings", settings_path, short: "S" %></nav>
          <%= form_with url: search_path, method: :get, class: "search-form", style: "display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px;", data: { turbo_action: "replace" } do %>
            <input type="text" name="q" value="<%= params[:q] %>" placeholder="search..." autocomplete="off" class="search-input" style="width: 200px; height: 22px; font-size: 13px; padding: 0 6px; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); background: var(--color-bg); color: var(--color-text); font-family: inherit;">
          <% end %>
          <% if Current.user.present? %>
            <%= button_to session_logout_path,
                  method: :delete,
                  form: { style: "margin-left: auto; display: inline;" },
                  class: "bracketed",
                  style: "background: none; border: none; padding: 0; font: inherit; color: inherit; cursor: pointer;" do %>[<span class="bl">logout</span>]<% end %>
          <% end %>
          <%# Visible affordance for the keyboard help modal (locked
              decision: keyboard-only audience is small, the link prevents
              the surface from being undiscoverable). Sits between the
              logout button and the theme toggle, mirroring the spec's
              "near the theme switcher" placement. The same modal is
              opened by pressing `?`. When no user is signed in, this
              link inherits the `margin-left: auto` previously carried by
              the theme toggle so the right-cluster still right-anchors. %>
          <span style="<%= Current.user.present? ? "" : "margin-left: auto;" %> display: inline-flex; align-items: center;">
            <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(label: "?", href: "#", data: { action: "click->keyboard#openHelp" }, active: false)) %>
          </span>
        <% end %>
        <a href="#" class="keycap keycap-theme" <%= 'style="margin-left: auto;"'.html_safe if content_for?(:hide_chrome) %> data-action="click->theme#toggle" data-theme-target="toggle">n</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <%= render "shared/flash_toasts" %>

    <%# Vertical gap above the breadcrumb / page heading is composed of
        two layers: this wrapper carries `padding-top` to clear the 32px
        fixed header (cannot drop below 32 without scrolling content
        under the navbar), and the inner `main` block carries an extra
        `padding-top` for breathing room. Restored 2026-05-05 after the
        previous tightening overshot to 0px and felt flush: the wrapper
        stays at the header-clearance minimum (32px) and the main block
        carries 16px of top padding so the first content row sits a
        consistent ~16px below the navbar whether the page renders a
        breadcrumb or jumps straight to a heading. Applied at the
        layout level so every page benefits without per-page
        overrides. %>
    <div style="padding-top: 32px;">
      <main style="padding: 16px 12px 8px 12px;">
        <% if content_for?(:breadcrumbs) %>
          <nav class="dot-list" style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><%= yield :breadcrumbs %><% if content_for?(:breadcrumb_actions) %><%= yield :breadcrumb_actions %><% end %></nav>
        <% end %>
        <%= yield %>
      </main>
    </div>

    <footer style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding: 8px 12px; margin-top: 24px;">
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px; font-size: 11px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <div class="dot-list">
          <% unless content_for?(:hide_chrome) %><span class="hide-mobile"><%= nav_link "home", root_path %></span><%= nav_link "channels", channels_path, short: "C" %><%= nav_link "videos", videos_path, short: "V" %><%= nav_link "projects", projects_path, short: "P" %><%= nav_link "settings", settings_path, short: "S" %><% end %>
          <a href="/" style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px; text-decoration: none; color: inherit;"><img src="/Pito.png" alt="Pito" style="height: 10px; width: auto; display: block; position: relative; top: -1px;"></a>
        </div>
        <span class="text-muted">&copy; <%= Date.current.year %><span class="hide-mobile"> &mdash; all rights reserved.</span></span>
        <span class="text-muted" style="margin-left: auto;"><%= version_label %></span>
      </div>
    </footer>

    <%# Keyboard shortcuts help modal — opened by `?` keypress or the
        `[ ? ]` link in the header. Mirrors `pito` CLI's help overlay
        per locked decision Q6. The dialog is the keyboard
        controller's `dialog` target; the controller is mounted on
        `<body>` so listeners live for the full page lifetime. %>
    <%= render(KeyboardShortcutsModalComponent.new) %>
  </body>
</html>
